<br> &nbsp;<br>
and the signature file:
<br> &nbsp;<br>
<a href="SIG">SIG</a> .


<br>
If you want to be sure of downloaded files authenticity, you should at least follow these steps:
<br>
<h6>
<pre>
wget FWP/TGZ
wget FWP/SIG
gpg --search 'dezperado autistici org'
# import the key from a trusted keyserver by following on screen instructions
gpg --verify SIG
</pre>
</h6>


<br> &nbsp;<br>
<h5>
The typical sequence of actions to build Fim, which should suffice is :
</h5>

<h6>
<pre>
tar xzf fim-VERSION.tar.gz 
cd fim-VERSION 
./configure --help=short 
# read the ./configure --help=short output : you can give options to ./configure
./configure 
make 
su -c "make install"
</pre>
</h6>


<h5>
Of course, there is a lot of
<a href="FIM.html">documentation</a> available
(here the <a href="README.html">README</a> page)
.
You are welcome to <a href="FIM.html#intro">browse</a> it even before downloading Fim.


<br> &nbsp;<br>
If you are interested at the SVN (subversion) <a href="REPOSITORY">repository</a>,
typing :
</h5>
<h6>
<pre>
svn export REPOSITORY
</pre>
</h6>
<h5>
at the command prompt will download the freshest (possibly unstable) version of Fim in a directory named 'fim'.
</h5>
